記述と一致している。s4では一括更新時の注意点について検証している。\n\nNow I'm checking the RST document structure for the binary data sections - there are multiple h2 headings covering search methods, registration methods, file content handling, and output operations. I'm analyzing the RST heading hierarchy more carefully now. The dashes under \"オブジェクトのフィールドの値の登録機能\" establish it as a subsection level, while the equals signs for \"1件のデータを更新する場合\" and \"複数件を更新する場合\" create another tier beneath that, following the pattern where the first character used defines each level in the document structure. Looking at the hints for each section now. Section 1 has the key classes covered like DbAccessSupport, SqlPStatement, and SqlResultSet, though the byte array return type itself isn't a class hint. Section 2 is partially listed but appears to include SqlPStatement, setBytes, setBinaryStream, and Blob among others.\n\nFor sections 3 and 4, I'm checking what class names are actually present versus what's missing from the hints. Section 3 is missing W11AE01Form, and section 4 is missing W11AE02Form—both are PascalCase classes that appear in the content but aren't captured in the hints. So across V4, there are two class names that should be added to make the hints more complete.\n\nI'm also noticing an important omission in the knowledge file: the source material mentions that while the example shows an INSERT statement, the same pattern applies equally to UPDATE and DELETE operations. This is a useful constraint to document since it clarifies the pattern's broader applicability beyond just INSERT, even though the code example itself is doing an INSERT. I'd consider this a minor gap since the section title does say \"更新\" (update), but the actual code demonstrates INSERT instead. The omission about executeUpdateByObject working for all DML operations—not just INSERT—is actually critical since it directly affects when and how to apply this pattern, which aligns with the guidance on technology selection. The missing form class names are minor details by comparison.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22468,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22468,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21fe8b1f-46cb-47bc-8bb9-c75768670127","uuid":"04fdd826-ed7f-4075-911d-961b5381d64c"}
